
// This Hyperlambda code checks if the value of the [forceAsText] node inside the [.arguments] node is equal to boolean true. If the condition is true, it sets the value of the [.text] node to boolean true using [set-value]. The [if] slot is used for conditional execution based on the result of the [eq] slot, which compares the values.
if
   eq:x:@.arguments/*/forceAsText
      .:bool:true
   .lambda
      set-value:x:@.text
         .:bool:true
